I should mention that Adam and I
are broadcasting live to you

00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:52.230
from New York.

00:00:52.230 --> 00:00:55.530
So let's get started with
Android Design in Action,

00:00:55.530 --> 00:00:59.200
Local Video and Rich
Notification.

00:00:59.200 --> 00:01:02.640
What we did today was we didn't
look at any specific

00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:06.070
local video players that
were previously

00:01:06.070 --> 00:01:07.270
reviewed in the App Clinic.

00:01:07.270 --> 00:01:09.510
I believe they're actually
re-doing that due to some sort

00:01:09.510 --> 00:01:11.280
of technical difficulties.

00:01:11.280 --> 00:01:14.110
But what we did today was,
instead of looking at specific

00:01:14.110 --> 00:01:20.390
apps, we came up with an example
app that did some

00:01:20.390 --> 00:01:23.270
similar things, but it wasn't
branded in any way.

00:01:23.270 --> 00:01:25.210
It's not kind of like
a published app.

00:01:25.210 --> 00:01:27.060
We have no intention
of publishing it.

00:01:27.060 --> 00:01:29.890
It's really just kind of a "what
if", you know, what if

00:01:29.890 --> 00:01:33.210
we were to design a local video
player from scratch.

00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:35.040
And we didn't do all
of the screens.

00:01:35.040 --> 00:01:38.530
We only did just a few of the
screens, primarily around the

00:01:38.530 --> 00:01:40.060
browse experience.

00:01:40.060 --> 00:01:43.890
We won't be talking too much
about video playback, because

00:01:43.890 --> 00:01:46.250
while you're playing the video,
there's a lot of things

00:01:46.250 --> 00:01:48.490
that you can really do.

00:01:48.490 --> 00:01:52.060
And we have some examples of
apps that do it really well.

00:01:52.060 --> 00:01:53.970
For example, the YouTube
App does a fairly

00:01:53.970 --> 00:01:54.930
good job with that.

00:01:54.930 --> 00:01:58.230
So if you already starting to
create a local video player or

00:01:58.230 --> 00:02:00.620
a video player in general, you
should probably model your

00:02:00.620 --> 00:02:04.250
playback screen after something
like YouTube.

00:02:04.250 --> 00:02:06.910
But what we did do is look
at browse screens

00:02:06.910 --> 00:02:08.720
and things like that.

