like Add to Queue just in

00:08:50.420 --> 00:08:52.290
case you want to-- or maybe
you'd call it like a Watch

00:08:52.290 --> 00:08:56.770
Later or something, just in
case you don't like watch

00:08:56.770 --> 00:08:58.032
right now, right then.

00:08:58.032 --> 00:09:00.410
NICK BUTCHER: Just to take off
one of his points, actually, I

00:09:00.410 --> 00:09:04.180
think the contextual action
bar is one of my favorite

00:09:04.180 --> 00:09:07.220
Android design paradigms because
it lends itself really

00:09:07.220 --> 00:09:09.590
well to handling not only
single selection but

00:09:09.590 --> 00:09:12.150
multiselection selection in
quite an elegant way, which I

00:09:12.150 --> 00:09:12.710
very much like.

00:09:12.710 --> 00:09:14.730
So if you long press on one
video from this Quick VIew,

00:09:14.730 --> 00:09:18.070
for example, you can see the
action bar will transform into

00:09:18.070 --> 00:09:20.540
options suitable for a single
video, so there might be

00:09:20.540 --> 00:09:23.540
different set of options
to support multiples.

00:09:23.540 --> 00:09:25.742
But then as you touch to select
more items within the

00:09:25.742 --> 00:09:28.440
grid, the action bar can then
refine its selections to just

00:09:28.440 --> 00:09:30.960
those actions suitable for
multiple, which is, I think, a

00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:33.190
very elegant kind of design
in the way it handles

00:09:33.190 --> 00:09:34.180
this sort of thing.

00:09:34.180 --> 00:09:37.190
ROMAN NURIK: And the other
thing is just users, in

00:09:37.190 --> 00:09:39.340
general, are very accustomed--
or Android users are very

00:09:39.340 --> 00:09:43.400
accustomed to using long press
to trigger context menus.

00:09:43.400 --> 00:09:46.470
And in our case, I mean, I guess
since Android 3.0, I

00:09:46.470 --> 00:09:50.370
guess even 4.0, we've
been using long

00:09:50.370 --> 00:09:52.400
press as really selection.

00:09:52.400 --> 00:09:56.040
And context, like entering
a selection context and

00:09:56.040 --> 00:09:59.030
providing extra actions, is
really kind of a secondary

00:09:59.030 --> 00:09:59.660
thing, right?

00:09:59.660 --> 00:10:02.480
So first, select the things you
want to act on, and then

00:10:02.480 --> 00:10:07.000
see the different options
available to you rather than

00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:09.860
long press and immediately
have options or actions

00:10:09.860 --> 00:10:13.235
available only on the view
you interacted with.

00:10:13.235 --> 00:10:15.940
NICK BUTCHER: Some examples of
that kind of behavior if you

00:10:15.940 --> 00:10:17.740
wanted to follow up and look
into that, I think Gallery

00:10:17.740 --> 00:10:21.071
does this quite nicely, and
Gmail also does a good job of

00:10:21.071 --> 00:10:23.105
this because of multiselection
behavior.

00:10:23.105 --> 00:10:25.360
ROMAN NURIK: And then we have a
bunch of open source code in

00:10:25.360 --> 00:10:29.790
the iOS, the iOSched project,
the Google I/O 2012 app that

00:10:29.790 --> 00:10:31.800
does multiple selection
and single

00:10:31.800 --> 00:10:34.451
selection action bullet.

