00:22:40.630 --> 00:22:43.560
of text than a normal
notification might.

00:22:43.560 --> 00:22:46.980
But with the additional
notifications, you can also

00:22:46.980 --> 00:22:50.630
get like a blank canvas and
draw whatever it is your

00:22:50.630 --> 00:22:51.570
application wants to do.

00:22:51.570 --> 00:22:53.930
So we revisited the TripAdvisor
app, which we took

00:22:53.930 --> 00:22:56.360
a look at a couple of weeks
back and envisaged

00:22:56.360 --> 00:22:57.020
what they could do.

00:22:57.020 --> 00:22:59.860
So here, that scenario we're
envisaging is someone's just

00:22:59.860 --> 00:23:03.080
arrived in a new city, and
they've detected this location

00:23:03.080 --> 00:23:06.930
change, and we're preemptively
offering them to see what is

00:23:06.930 --> 00:23:09.095
going on in the attractions
around them.

00:23:09.095 --> 00:23:11.120
So, straight away in the
minimized version, you just

00:23:11.120 --> 00:23:12.300
say, well, welcome to London.

00:23:12.300 --> 00:23:13.680
It says, see nearby
attractions.

00:23:13.680 --> 00:23:16.915
But if we were to swipe down,
we can actually provide a

00:23:16.915 --> 00:23:19.810
completely custom layout
within the

00:23:19.810 --> 00:23:20.670
notification itself.

00:23:20.670 --> 00:23:24.530
So here we're displaying two
tiles, like picking out the

00:23:24.530 --> 00:23:26.740
top two near attractions near
the user where they've just

00:23:26.740 --> 00:23:29.230
arrived in a new city, which
might be kind of fun.

00:23:29.230 --> 00:23:31.610
But yet, really, this is
just a window into your

00:23:31.610 --> 00:23:31.970
application.

00:23:31.970 --> 00:23:34.640
So you can completely extend
your branding, your look and

00:23:34.640 --> 00:23:37.830
feel right into the
notification bar.

00:23:37.830 --> 00:23:39.710
ROMAN NURIK: Yeah, and then one
thing you can offer here,

00:23:39.710 --> 00:23:44.390
again, as further actions may
be see all, or search for a

00:23:44.390 --> 00:23:45.100
specific area.

00:23:45.100 --> 00:23:48.910
Like if for some reason the app
accidentally just didn't

00:23:48.910 --> 00:23:52.250
get your location right, you
could say, choose a different

00:23:52.250 --> 00:23:53.700
location or something
like that.

00:23:53.700 --> 00:23:56.230
So providing actions, I mean,
almost always there are

00:23:56.230 --> 00:23:59.650
multiple things you can
do on notifications.

00:23:59.650 --> 00:24:05.000
Providing extra actions, it's
just a really, really easy way

00:24:05.000 --> 00:24:07.570
to provide extra functionality
without much effort.

00:24:07.570 --> 00:24:09.780
NICK BUTCHER: It's one of my
favorite functions on Android.

00:24:09.780 --> 00:24:12.240
So it means it leads to less
jumping around between

00:24:12.240 --> 00:24:12.800
applications.

00:24:12.800 --> 00:24:15.080
I no longer have to come and go
in and out, in and out, and

00:24:15.080 --> 00:24:17.660
have these context switches
all the time.

00:24:17.660 --> 00:24:19.920
With the introduction of rich
notifications, I find myself

00:24:19.920 --> 00:24:22.130
processing information and
staying on top of things and

00:24:22.130 --> 00:24:24.830
doing quick actions straight
from the notification.

00:24:24.830 --> 00:24:25.930
I find it really satisfying.

00:24:25.930 --> 00:24:28.180
It makes me feel super
productive and powerful.

00:24:28.180 --> 00:24:30.870
So I really encourage designers
and developers to

00:24:30.870 --> 00:24:33.140
think about how you can use
this newly expanded

00:24:33.140 --> 00:24:34.846
functionality in your apps.

