00:28:27.250 --> 00:28:30.670
So when a user first opens the
app, if there's something

00:28:30.670 --> 00:28:33.150
that's very difficult to
discover, then you may

00:28:33.150 --> 00:28:35.450
want to show this.

00:28:35.450 --> 00:28:39.820
Before you jump in and start
using it, you should read our

00:28:39.820 --> 00:28:43.080
design pattern on Help, which
talks about the specific cases

00:28:43.080 --> 00:28:44.670
where you should use something
like this.

00:28:44.670 --> 00:28:47.410
In general, you should try
avoiding on-screen tutorials

00:28:47.410 --> 00:28:49.330
or things, because your
interface should

00:28:49.330 --> 00:28:50.270
just explain itself.

00:28:50.270 --> 00:28:51.670
And if there's a problem
