Maps add-on.

00:30:25.070 --> 00:30:28.570
And it basically gives you
things like a standardized

00:30:28.570 --> 00:30:32.160
on-screen My Location buttons,
standardized on-screen Zoom

00:30:32.160 --> 00:30:38.960
buttons, and also standardized
on-screen Info bubbles, so

00:30:38.960 --> 00:30:41.080
bubbles or balloons or whatever
you want to call them

00:30:41.080 --> 00:30:44.216
that pop up above markers
when you touch them.

00:30:44.216 --> 00:30:47.190
NICK BUTCHER: So I really like
this for a couple of reasons.

00:30:47.190 --> 00:30:49.770
Not only will it make your
developers' lives easier to

00:30:49.770 --> 00:30:52.400
implement mapping features,
but for me, it also really

00:30:52.400 --> 00:30:54.090
standardizes the interactions,
like to be

00:30:54.090 --> 00:30:55.230
very similar to Maps.

00:30:55.230 --> 00:30:57.850
Maps is probably one of the
most used apps on Android.

00:30:57.850 --> 00:31:01.440
And if you deviate from the
patterns where they're going

00:31:01.440 --> 00:31:04.320
to locate new buttons or how
balloons pop up and so on,

00:31:04.320 --> 00:31:06.690
then your app's going to
just feel slightly off.

00:31:06.690 --> 00:31:09.490
And I think using this Polaris
library will really help in

00:31:09.490 --> 00:31:12.636
getting that consistent feel.

